    <abstract>
      <t>Path Segment is a type of Segment Routing (SR) segment, and a Path Segment Identifier (PSID) is used to identify an SR path. Path Segment can be used in an SR over MPLS (SR-MPLS) data plane. This document provides Target Forwarding Equivalence Class (FEC) Stack TLV and sub-TLV definitions for PSID.</t>
